{"title":"Amazon refreshes its monochrome Kindle lineup, including a bigger Paperwhite","link":"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2024/10/amazon-refreshes-its-monochrome-kindle-lineup-including-a-bigger-paperwhite/","date":1729083658000,"content":"<p>Amazon is shaking up <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/kindlefamily\">its entire Kindle e-reader lineup</a> today, at least by the slow-moving and relatively placid standards of the e-reader market. The company is announcing a major refresh to the <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CZ9VFQ2P\">pen-centric Kindle Scribe</a>, a screen-size bump for <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CFPJYX7P\">the mainstream Kindle Paperwhite</a>, and small tweaks to <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CNV9F72P\">the basic Kindle</a>â€”a rare simultaneous refresh for devices that the company usually updates one or two at a time.</p>\n<p>In addition to the monochrome e-readers, Amazon introduced its first color e-reader today. The new <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CN3XR57P\">Kindle Colorsoft</a>, covered in more detail <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2024/10/amazons-first-color-kindle-e-reader-the-kindle-colorsoft-will-run-you-280\">here</a>, looks almost identical to the new Paperwhite and launches on October 30 for $279.99.</p>\n<h2>Enhanced e-readers</h2>\n<figure>\n      <img width=\"640\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Tungsten-3-640x640.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Tungsten-3-640x640.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Tungsten-3-300x300.jpg 300w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Tungsten-3-150x150.jpg 150w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Tungsten-3-768x768.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Tungsten-3-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Tungsten-3-2048x2048.jpg 2048w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Tungsten-3-500x500.jpg 500w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Tungsten-3-1000x1000.jpg 1000w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Tungsten-3-980x980.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Tungsten-3-1440x1440.jpg 1440w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      The new Kindle Scribe in the gray \"Tungsten\" finish. \n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n          \n          Amazon\n\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n      <figure>\n      <img width=\"640\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Metallic-Jade-4-640x640.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Metallic-Jade-4-640x640.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Metallic-Jade-4-300x300.jpg 300w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Metallic-Jade-4-150x150.jpg 150w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Metallic-Jade-4-768x768.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Metallic-Jade-4-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Metallic-Jade-4-2048x2048.jpg 2048w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Metallic-Jade-4-500x500.jpg 500w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Metallic-Jade-4-1000x1000.jpg 1000w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Metallic-Jade-4-980x980.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Metallic-Jade-4-1440x1440.jpg 1440w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      A new \"metallic jade\" finish. \n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n          \n          Amazon\n\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n      <figure>\n      <img width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Active-Canvas-640x360.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Active-Canvas-640x360.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Active-Canvas-300x169.jpg 300w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Active-Canvas-768x432.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Active-Canvas-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Active-Canvas-384x216.jpg 384w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Active-Canvas-1152x648.jpg 1152w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Active-Canvas-980x551.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Active-Canvas-1440x810.jpg 1440w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Active-Canvas.jpg 1920w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      The \"Active Canvas\" note-taking feature, which will display notes inline and reflow text around them.\n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n          \n          Amazon\n\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n      <figure>\n      <img width=\"640\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Covers-640x640.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Covers-640x640.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Covers-300x300.jpg 300w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Covers-150x150.jpg 150w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Covers-768x768.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Covers-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Covers-2048x2048.jpg 2048w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Covers-500x500.jpg 500w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Covers-1000x1000.jpg 1000w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Covers-980x980.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Scribe-Covers-1440x1440.jpg 1440w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      Covers for the Kindle Scribe.\n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n          \n          Amazon\n\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n  \n<p>Going from most to least significant: The new Kindle Scribe's upgrades are mostly meant to make it a more paper-like writing experience. It has a new textured screen coating, a white screen bezel that blends into the screen (we've also seen this deployed in tablets like <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2024/09/new-color-e-ink-remarkable-tablet-tries-to-catch-up-with-and-leapfrog-kindle-scribe/\">the reMarkable Paper Pro</a>), and a tweaked Premium Pen accessory with a \"new soft-tipped eraser\" that feels more like an actual pencil eraser.</p><p><a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2024/10/amazon-refreshes-its-monochrome-kindle-lineup-including-a-bigger-paperwhite/\">Read full article</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2024/10/amazon-refreshes-its-monochrome-kindle-lineup-including-a-bigger-paperwhite/#comments\">Comments</a></p>","author":"Andrew Cunningham","siteTitle":"Ars Technica","siteHash":"5b0ddf6e8923e49262a7894cfd77962733e43fbcc565a103b48373820b310636","entryHash":"026dae8e1eee05d805f6b5cf7af85d37667a6b978c843bd2b9c8dbb7472f3f97","category":"Tech"}